Police are attempting to find out how a 43-year-old man came to be seriously injured in Glasgow city centre.
The man was found with head and facial injuries in Midland Street, just off Jamaica Street, at 23:45 on Saturday.
He was taken by ambulance to Glasgow Royal Infirmary where he remains in a serious condition.
Police have appealed for anyone who was in or near Midland Street around the time the man was found, and who may have information, to come forward.
